name: Air Alchemy Coin
description:
The Air symbol in alchemy is considered to represent the holy, life-giving forces and sources of life. The symbol is often represented using blue and white. 

1/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Water Alchemy Coin
description:
The Water symbol mainly represents intuition and is associated with the mercury element in alchemy. Greek philosopher Plato associated it with properties like wetness, moist and cold and the color blue is linked to the element. Combined with the alchemical fire symbol, they comprise the Seal of Solomon. 

2/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Fire Alchemy Coin
description:
The Fire symbol represents emotions like love, passion, compassion, hate, anger etc., the ones we would call 'the fiery' emotions. The symbol also symbolizes rising energy which is sometimes associated with aspiring to reach the divine above us. Combined with the alchemical water symbol, they comprise the Seal of Solomon. 

3/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Earth Alchemy Coin
description:
Greek philosopher Plato associated properties like cold and dryness with the Earth symbol while brown and green are the colors representing the element. The alchemical Earth is also considered as a symbol for physical sensations or mechanical movement. 

4/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Salt Alchemy Coin
description:
Salt in alchemy represents crystallization and condensation and it was also considered as a symbol for the physical matter and essence of things in nature. A circle of salt is believed to be protective of evil energies or spirits. 

5/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Silver Alchemy Coin
description:
Silver was associated with the Moon, representing ease of mind, stillness and the human brain. 

6/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Gold Alchemy Coin
description:
Gold was associated with the Sun, representing perfection, prosperity, wealth and general well-being both in the physical and spiritual. It also represents the heart. 

7/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Sulfur Alchemy Coin
description:
Sulfur, also known as Brimstone, represented dissolution, evaporation and expansive force in alchemy. It is often also used to represent the Satanic. 

8/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Phosporus Alchemy Coin
description:
Phosporus was believed to have the capability of capturing light. It is often related to light and darknes and the human spirit or soul. 

9/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Arsenic Alchemy Coin
description:
Antimony is considered as a symbol for the wild and free parts of human nature. It's also often represented with swans. 

10/11 Alchemy Collection

name: Philosopher's Stone Coin
description:
The Philosopher's stone is a legendary substance in alchemy which is believed to have capabilities that can turn common base metals like mercury into rare and expensive ones such as gold and silver. It represents enlightenment, heavenly bliss and perfection in alchemy. Creating the stone was the ultimate goal in alchemy. The stone was also believed to have rejuvenating powers and could be used to become immortal. 

11/11 Alchemy Collection
